          ],
          "parameters": {
            "color": 5,
            "width": 592,
            "height": 352,
            "content": "# Hacker News Trend Tracking\rTrack popular via https://hn.algolia.com/api\r\r## Sliding Window\rTimer (Trigger): Run every 4 hours. Lookback: Fetch data from the past 24 hours.\r\r- Define a rule—\"Posts published less than 1 hour ago and with extremely low interaction (<3 points) are considered noise and should be discarded directly.\"\r- If a post receives 20 likes in just 10 minutes (extremely explosive), we should keep it; but if it only gets 1 like after 10 minutes (normal situation), we temporarily ignore it and wait for the next scheduled task (e.g., 4 hours later) to evaluate it when it \"matures.\""
          },
          "typeVersion": 1
        },
